OL,3,CThree people die in Listeria outbreak
OL,4,Clinked to desserts
OL,6,F"Most people who are affected by
OL,7,Flisteriosis will have no symptoms or
OL,8,Fexperience mild diarrhoea which
OL,9,Fsubsides in a few days.
OL,11,F"Those who are more vulnerable like
OL,12,Fthe severely immunocompromised or
OL,13,Fthose with advanced aged can be at
OL,14,Frisk of severe illness such as
OL,15,Fmeningitis and life-threatening sepsis.
OL,17,F"Listeriosis in pregnancy can cause
OL,18,Fvery serious illness in mothers and
OL,19,Ftheir babies, and in babies up to one
OL,20,Fmonth old."
